WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:03.739
Thank you for downloading or streaming this message from Immanuel Church.

00:04.160 --> 00:08.648
We are one church with multiple locations, and we believe God wants to bless you right where you are.

00:08.688 --> 00:14.799
In a few moments, you're going to hear some practical teaching from God's Word that I believe will be inspiring and relevant to your life.

00:15.560 --> 00:25.458
First, though, if you haven't yet experienced Immanuel Live, we encourage you to go to our website, eclive.org, to check out our service times and locations so that you can experience Immanuel in person

00:25.538 --> 00:26.761
or through our online campus.

00:27.462 --> 00:36.242
If this message blesses you and you'd like to support the ministry financially, again, you can go to eclive.org and click on the giving tab and choose online campus at your campus.

00:36.924 --> 00:41.554
Thanks again for joining us today and we hope this message will be an encouragement to you on your spiritual journey.

00:44.706 --> 00:56.620
to take a minute and welcome all of our locations right now, our Band of Canvas, Franklin campus, our Garfield Park campus, our online campus, our locations over at the Theodore House and also the Johnson County Work Release.

00:56.660 --> 00:59.803
Can we give it up for all of our locations, including here at Greenwood?

01:00.664 --> 01:01.845
Welcome, welcome, welcome.

01:03.247 --> 01:04.789
We're going to have so many locations soon.

01:04.849 --> 01:09.394
I'm not going to be able to remember all of them, so I'm going to get there.

01:09.474 --> 01:11.597
We are in a series right now called Upgrade.

01:11.617 --> 01:17.624
Now before I jump back into week number three of our series, I just want to let you know that I am having a fantastic morning.

01:18.145 --> 01:18.766
I really am.

01:18.806 --> 01:19.987
I'm super energized.

01:20.828 --> 01:31.041
And the reason why I am really having a great morning today is because last night my son's team won for the first time ever Greenwood Christian Academy won the county championship tournament.

01:31.682 --> 01:38.130
And so very, very exciting highlight of my fatherhood

01:38.306 --> 01:41.411
And I didn't even do anything.

01:42.412 --> 01:44.395
But so my son's team played great.

01:44.415 --> 01:47.079
They're head coach Jordan Johnny Marlon's a fantastic coach.

01:47.099 --> 01:48.321
They just played wonderful.

01:48.361 --> 01:49.863
The boys did a great job.

01:49.903 --> 01:53.128
And so I'm ultra super excited.

01:53.428 --> 01:57.134
And so you might just get the best sermon you've ever heard today, OK?

01:58.456 --> 02:03.664
So I know life is not about basketball, but basketball is pretty important.

02:03.684 --> 02:05.266
And I'm just kidding.

02:05.378 --> 02:08.323
So if you're new here, like I said, we're in a series called Upgrade.

02:08.343 --> 02:11.930
And I want to start with a little bit of a flashback from my childhood.

02:12.010 --> 02:16.037
I remember my childhood, a big part of it was Legos.

02:16.438 --> 02:17.460
Anybody else grow up?

02:18.422 --> 02:21.086
And just Legos were a big deal.

02:21.167 --> 02:22.549
And they're super old, too.

02:22.589 --> 02:23.350
I didn't even realize this.

02:23.411 --> 02:27.538
But Legos have been around since, gosh, I think the 1930s.

02:27.586 --> 02:32.130
But my family had two really large bags of Legos.

02:32.430 --> 02:33.932
I mean, like laundry bags.

02:34.432 --> 02:45.682
And so it was a weekly occurrence that my brothers and I, we'd get our Legos out, we'd spread them all over the floor, and we'd spend hours building some sort of ship or car and had guns and wheels.

02:45.762 --> 02:48.004
And two hours later, we'd have this awesome ship.

02:48.044 --> 02:50.005
And then we'd break it up.

02:50.066 --> 02:52.728
We'd keep it for a little while, and we'd break it up and put everything back in the bag.

02:52.748 --> 02:54.750
And that was just something that we did.

02:54.770 --> 02:55.450
It was a lot of fun.

02:55.490 --> 02:57.572
And today, kids

02:57.552 --> 02:59.756
kids play with Legos, but it's a little bit different.

02:59.776 --> 03:03.343
Have you noticed that the Legos actually come, you know, like this.

03:04.004 --> 03:05.166
And this is an example.

03:05.427 --> 03:08.793
Like back in our day, you just got Legos and you built something from your head.

03:09.174 --> 03:13.381
Like now it's like, no, build this, you know, and it's like, I don't know what's the matter with kids today.

03:13.442 --> 03:15.345
Maybe they lack creativity or something.

03:15.425 --> 03:15.826
I don't know.

03:15.906 --> 03:16.968
Just kidding, just kidding.

03:16.988 --> 03:18.771
Anyway, it's obviously to make money.

03:19.933 --> 03:21.115
But this is a great example.

03:21.275 --> 03:28.067
And if you have kids or grandkids, you've probably worked with them on building something like this for their birthday or for Christmas or whatever.

03:28.628 --> 03:32.014
And it's kind of a difficult thing to do.

03:32.394 --> 03:36.882
It's so challenging that they actually give you a 100-page manual.

03:37.058 --> 03:37.639
to follow.

03:37.699 --> 03:38.340
Have you seen these?

03:38.560 --> 03:39.441
Like, no, I'm not kidding.

03:39.461 --> 03:46.330
When I say 100 pages, there are literally 100 pages in this thing with step-by-step instructions to follow.

03:46.951 --> 03:50.255
And if you don't follow these instructions, guess what happens?

03:50.436 --> 03:53.159
You don't get to build, you don't get to build the ship.

03:53.459 --> 03:56.764
In this goal, this right here, this is actually the real ship, the Millennium Falcon.

03:57.405 --> 03:57.925
Super cool.

03:58.907 --> 04:01.490
And I didn't have anything like this when I was a kid.

04:01.538 --> 04:02.319
But did you guys?

04:02.660 --> 04:03.641
No, I don't think, yeah.

04:03.661 --> 04:05.584
So this actually opens up in that fun.

04:05.844 --> 04:07.527
Like you can actually see inside.

04:07.847 --> 04:13.636
Like that's where Han Solo and Chewbacca would hang out and play that little chess game, whatever it was that they were playing.

04:14.417 --> 04:19.124
But if you look really closely, you can see Chewy and Solo right in there.

04:19.284 --> 04:20.245
That's kinda, you can't see it.

04:20.285 --> 04:21.447
But anyway, super cool.

04:21.627 --> 04:29.138
And if you don't follow the instructions on in the manual to build this thing, that it's gonna be a challenge

04:30.050 --> 04:34.577
It's going to be a challenge to get the end result, to get what's on the box here.

04:34.597 --> 04:35.879
And so that's why they give this to you.

04:35.939 --> 04:42.089
And I want to talk a little bit today about the concept of following instructions.

04:43.311 --> 04:44.934
We're in a series called Upgrade.

04:45.014 --> 04:50.002
And what we said in this series is that, you know, around this time of the year, we'd all like to take our lives to the next level.

04:50.338 --> 05:01.197
We'd all like to improve our physical health and fitness, our relationship with God, or maybe overcome some sort of emotion that's been plaguing us, or maybe kick a bad habit or an addiction.

05:02.479 --> 05:04.242
And so we set goals in New Year's resolutions.

05:04.262 --> 05:07.768
The only problem is we struggle to follow through, we struggle to fail.

05:07.808 --> 05:10.994
So what we said is, what if we look back at the story of the Israelites

05:11.106 --> 05:13.829
who had probably the greatest upgrade in the Bible.

05:13.849 --> 05:16.952
They moved out of 400 years of slavery into the Promised Land.

05:16.972 --> 05:23.319
What if we looked at their story and just pulled out some principles and then applied them to our lives so that we too can experience an upgrade?

05:23.379 --> 05:25.742
So we talked about week one, extreme clarity.

05:26.042 --> 05:27.884
Last week we talked about pushing our limits.

05:28.205 --> 05:31.428
If you missed either one of those talks, you can go to our YouTube channel.

05:31.468 --> 05:32.109
Yes, that's right.

05:32.429 --> 05:33.871
Emmanuel's now has a YouTube channel.

05:34.111 --> 05:36.233
You can check it out and look at those two talks.

05:36.293 --> 05:40.498
But today, I want to talk about this concept of following

05:40.578 --> 05:41.680
Instructions in your notes.

05:41.700 --> 05:42.301
I wrote it like this.

05:42.421 --> 05:43.723
Third principle of an upgrade.

05:43.763 --> 05:45.906
We're going to look at this in the story of Joshua in the Israelites.

05:46.327 --> 05:49.932
An upgrade will require, say it with me, obedience.

05:49.992 --> 05:53.338
Now that word obedience is not a sexy word.

05:53.438 --> 05:54.720
It's not a popular word.

05:54.780 --> 05:55.861
It's not a fun word.

05:55.901 --> 05:56.282
Do you agree?

05:56.302 --> 05:59.287
It's like, that's God's what kind of word that is.

05:59.347 --> 06:01.490
It's like, really, do I have to do what you say?

06:01.634 --> 06:03.117
Do I have to follow the boss?

06:03.137 --> 06:10.510
Do I have to do it with my mom and dad, say it almost has a negative connotation, but I want to try to change that perspective for you today.

06:10.550 --> 06:15.699
Every single upgrade is going to require obedience.

06:15.719 --> 06:21.970
You know, when I would help my kids with these little projects, with the Lego projects for Christmas,

06:22.050 --> 06:28.181
When you get to, you know, I don't know, step 24 or so, it kind of repeats itself.

06:28.281 --> 06:35.634
Like, there's a series of steps for one side of the ship and then there's a series of steps for the other side of the ship and the top of the ship and the bottom.

06:35.654 --> 06:37.437
And it can get a little bit redundant.

06:37.497 --> 06:46.834
And so sometimes, because I'm such a smart guy, I just think to myself, well, I've already seen these steps, I'll just wing it.

06:48.066 --> 06:52.912
And several times I've put down the instructional manual, and I've just kind of said, well, I know where this piece goes.

06:52.952 --> 06:55.715
I've already done this once, and so I start to put it together by myself.

06:55.775 --> 07:02.563
And only to find out 17 steps later that I missed a step.

07:02.583 --> 07:03.064
Have you been there?

07:03.845 --> 07:05.347
Maybe it was with IKEA furniture.

07:07.269 --> 07:08.771
Maybe you've never put a Lego together.

07:08.951 --> 07:11.754
But you get IKEA furniture out and you're like, I don't need this stupid manual.

07:11.815 --> 07:14.738
So you start to do it because you think you're smart.

07:15.842 --> 07:18.746
And then you get to step five and you're like, oh, listen, look right.

07:18.766 --> 07:21.350
This table is not supposed to shape this way.

07:21.971 --> 07:23.754
It doesn't look like the picture on the box.

07:24.615 --> 07:31.785
Well, you decided, and what I decided, and I do it all the time, I just decided to wing it, to kind of do it on my own.

07:32.426 --> 07:37.874
And here's what I'm telling you today as a pastor, and I see this so many times as a pastor of a church.

07:38.306 --> 07:40.789
People come into me, and this is my own life as well.

07:40.849 --> 07:44.674
It's not judging anybody, but people come to me and they say, hey, I need help with my marriage.

07:44.694 --> 07:48.579
I need help with my relationship with my son, my daughter, my finances are a mess.

07:48.679 --> 07:50.261
We're about to get a divorce to this and that.

07:50.622 --> 07:55.308
I'm having anxiety and worry and I can't even function at work and all I do is sleep.

07:56.669 --> 08:03.538
And what has happened is their life is not looking like they wanted it to because

08:03.842 --> 08:15.679
At some point, you and I have decided to skip a bunch of steps because we thought we knew better when it came to parenting or when it comes to finances or when it comes to sexuality.

08:16.140 --> 08:18.383
You were like, you know what?

08:18.403 --> 08:19.845
I kind of know what the Bible says.

08:20.185 --> 08:23.590
And I went to Sunday school, but I think I got it.

08:24.832 --> 08:26.254
So I'm just going to put this book away.

08:26.294 --> 08:27.656
It's a little bit archaic anyway.

08:27.676 --> 08:29.659
I mean, is it really relevant for today?

08:29.719 --> 08:31.762
I mean, come on, it's so old.

08:32.418 --> 08:36.662
Does God really know about how I should handle my sexuality?

08:38.063 --> 08:39.365
Does God really know about money?

08:39.405 --> 08:42.007
Did Jesus really know about handling finances?

08:42.027 --> 08:43.389
I mean, it was so long ago.

08:43.729 --> 08:46.592
Let me just put it down and I will do it my way.

08:46.652 --> 08:49.635
And then 16 steps later, we're going, this isn't working out.

08:49.875 --> 08:50.856
Let me go call somebody.

08:50.876 --> 08:51.897
Let me go talk to somebody.

08:52.657 --> 08:53.879
You know what the problem is with me?

08:53.959 --> 08:55.280
And this is me, I'll just throw myself.

08:56.141 --> 08:59.344
I kind of think I know how to do things.

09:00.505 --> 09:01.586
And so I just do it

09:02.082 --> 09:02.903
my way.

09:03.023 --> 09:04.084
I don't follow the instructions.

09:04.124 --> 09:14.434
Listen to what God told Joshua in regards to getting into the Promised Land, in regards to cross after they crossed the Jordan River and get into the Promised Land, listen to what Joshua, God tells Joshua in Joshua 1 verse 7.

09:14.874 --> 09:16.235
Be strong and very courageous.

09:16.255 --> 09:17.356
We covered that last week.

09:17.416 --> 09:17.597
Why?

09:17.657 --> 09:19.498
Because we're going to have to push past our limits.

09:19.518 --> 09:21.180
We're going to have to do things we've never done before.

09:21.620 --> 09:23.702
And it's going to be fear, it's going to bring fear and doubt.

09:23.762 --> 09:25.184
So we have to be strong and courageous.

09:25.985 --> 09:27.266
Watch the next sentence.

09:27.286 --> 09:30.068
Be careful to say with me all of our campuses.

09:31.210 --> 09:31.730
Okay.

09:32.994 --> 09:39.483
Be careful to obey all of the instructions that Moses gave you in Genesis, Exodus, Leviticus, Numbers, Deuteronomy.

09:39.883 --> 09:41.786
That's what Moses gave Joshua.

09:41.806 --> 09:45.491
Be careful to follow everything that Moses gave you in the Pentateuch.

09:45.511 --> 09:47.053
That's the first five books of the Bible.

09:48.835 --> 09:54.863
If you do that and you don't fail to deviate, don't deviate from them turning either to the right or to the left.

09:55.104 --> 09:57.166
Don't skip any steps, Josh.

09:58.388 --> 10:02.834
When you do that, if you do that, if you obey,

10:03.362 --> 10:06.125
you'll be successful in everything you do.

10:07.045 --> 10:08.767
Wow.

10:08.787 --> 10:21.059
I would have thought he would have said, you know, Joshua, you have to get up every morning and you have to train all of the men who are 20 and older how to kill with a sword.

10:21.079 --> 10:24.222
And you have to make a bunch of armor because you don't have any armor.

10:24.582 --> 10:32.489
And if you will make swords and armor and if you will practice and get them battle ready, then you will be successful.

10:32.509 --> 10:33.330
That's not what he says.

10:34.178 --> 10:34.859
I would have said that.

10:36.320 --> 10:42.007
He says, no, no, no, just obey what Moses told you and you'll be successful.

10:42.407 --> 10:43.829
Listen to what the prophet Isaiah said.

10:44.129 --> 10:45.210
Isaiah 1, verse 19.

10:46.011 --> 10:51.598
If you are willing and obedient, you'll eat the good things of the land.

10:51.638 --> 10:59.026
God is looking for people who simply say, yes, sir, whatever you say, I'll do it just like

10:59.202 --> 11:00.063
You said, now why?

11:00.464 --> 11:01.044
Well, how is it?

11:01.405 --> 11:05.670
I have one of those minds where it's like, I read something in the Bible, but I'm like, yeah, but how does that work?

11:07.172 --> 11:09.374
I hear you, but why does that work that way?

11:09.574 --> 11:10.936
Anybody else have a mind like that?

11:10.996 --> 11:12.658
I'm always looking at things from that day.

11:12.678 --> 11:14.881
Like, I see something, but I wanna know why.

11:15.381 --> 11:17.084
That's why I used to drive my mom nuts.

11:17.884 --> 11:19.306
Why do I have to do that?

11:19.406 --> 11:22.830
You tell a kid to do something and they're like, why?

11:22.991 --> 11:23.331
That's me.

11:24.312 --> 11:25.654
Okay, God, why does it work this way?

11:26.074 --> 11:27.076
Three reasons, number one.

11:27.476 --> 11:29.138
When we obey, guess what?

11:30.018 --> 11:31.921
God's power is activated.

11:32.041 --> 11:38.249
God's divine power is activated when we simply obey Him.

11:39.131 --> 11:41.414
Think about what God told Joshua about Jericho.

11:41.895 --> 11:53.811
Hey, walk around the city once every day for six days and then walk around the city seven times on the seventh day and after the seventh lap blow the horns and shout and I will activate my power and bring the walls down.

11:55.253 --> 11:58.738
God's power was dependent upon the obedience

11:59.234 --> 12:00.215
of the Israelites.

12:00.576 --> 12:02.419
I don't even know that I can explain that.

12:03.060 --> 12:05.804
I just know that that's what's there in the scripture.

12:06.345 --> 12:13.014
That when we obey God, he says, I'm gonna unlock, unleash my divine favor in your life.

12:13.034 --> 12:16.279
There's a great story in the book of Luke chapter five.

12:16.780 --> 12:26.194
Jesus is preaching on the shore and Peter and his fishermen crew had fished all night so they had left their boats on the side.

12:26.306 --> 12:33.415
And so Jesus is preaching on the sand and the crowd is pressing in on him and they're like almost pushing him in the water.

12:33.475 --> 12:37.860
So he gets in one of the boats and kind of gets into the water and he continues his sermon.

12:38.201 --> 12:42.426
And then after his sermon's done and everybody kind of disperses, listen to what he says to Peter.

12:43.667 --> 12:49.595
He says, now Peter, I want you to go out and back out into where the water's deep and let down your nets to catch some fish.

12:49.655 --> 12:51.497
Now Peter had fished all night.

12:51.677 --> 12:52.799
So listen to what he says.

12:54.040 --> 12:55.602
Master, Simon replied.

12:56.130 --> 13:00.595
We worked hard all last night and we didn't catch one fish.

13:03.257 --> 13:03.958
Not a thing.

13:05.279 --> 13:07.962
Now Jesus, think about what, think about Peter's mindset.

13:07.982 --> 13:13.267
I know that you work with wood and you make tables and chairs and you're a carpenter and that's awesome.

13:13.287 --> 13:13.968
Weed of fishermen.

13:15.610 --> 13:18.913
And I know about fish and I know when they bite and when they don't bite.

13:19.053 --> 13:21.276
And we've been out there laboring all night in the cold.

13:21.296 --> 13:23.698
We haven't caught one fish.

13:23.778 --> 13:25.681
Are you sure you know what you're talking about?

13:25.861 --> 13:27.804
I'm not so sure you do.

13:29.787 --> 13:32.511
Nevertheless, watch this.

13:33.833 --> 13:36.337
And wouldn't it be wonderful if this were the mantra of our lives?

13:38.881 --> 13:46.853
Nevertheless, if you say so, I will go out and let my nets down again.

13:48.655 --> 13:49.216
Watch what happens.

13:50.818 --> 13:53.202
And this time their nets were so full of fish,

13:53.858 --> 13:55.560
that the nets began to tear.

13:56.361 --> 14:06.375
With a shout, watch this, Peter's partners come out with another boat and soon as they're putting their fish in the boat, both boats began sinking.

14:07.497 --> 14:10.621
I read, when I read this stuff, I'm like, wow.

14:12.624 --> 14:16.950
All Peter did was say, if you say so, I will do it.

14:17.831 --> 14:21.716
And God's power shows up and all these fish start to jump in the net.

14:21.817 --> 14:22.898
I don't know why.

14:23.138 --> 14:26.282
Listen, I'm not telling you, you know, I understand this.

14:26.923 --> 14:30.408
I'm just telling you what happened and what caused it.

14:30.668 --> 14:33.271
Peter said, I will do what you say.

14:33.512 --> 14:34.133
I will obey.

14:34.233 --> 14:36.676
Joshua said, I will do what you said.

14:36.996 --> 14:40.942
And God's power is activated when we simply obey.

14:41.142 --> 14:42.564
You know what Peter does after this happens?

14:42.584 --> 14:47.070
He gets down on his knees and he bows low and he says, depart from me, Jesus.

14:47.450 --> 14:48.352
I'm a sinful man.

14:49.473 --> 14:50.194
Why?

14:50.690 --> 14:53.014
He obeyed with a doubt in his heart.

14:53.334 --> 14:56.118
He's like, I don't think you know what you're talking about.

14:57.080 --> 14:58.261
Like we're the fishermen.

14:58.362 --> 14:59.904
We fished all night, didn't catch a thing.

15:00.445 --> 15:01.306
You're the carpenter.

15:03.409 --> 15:09.118
But if you say so, I'll let down the nets.

15:09.138 --> 15:10.760
What if that was the mantra of your life?

15:11.241 --> 15:14.546
See, we live in a culture today where a lot of people read this book

15:17.378 --> 15:20.703
I don't think he knows what he's talking about.

15:20.723 --> 15:23.648
I mean, people don't, people live with each other today.

15:23.708 --> 15:26.212
Like they move in and have sex before marriage.

15:27.594 --> 15:31.240
Like doesn't God know that you can save a lot of money that way?

15:31.661 --> 15:35.246
Like doesn't he understand you have to test drive the car before you buy?

15:35.266 --> 15:37.370
Like where are you at?

15:37.390 --> 15:39.012
You're not even relevant anymore.

15:39.052 --> 15:43.740
Now you want me to wait until marriage before we live together and have sex?

15:44.261 --> 15:45.202
Are you crazy?

15:46.242 --> 15:49.305
What if you simply said, you know what?

15:51.327 --> 15:52.548
That doesn't really make sense to me.

15:54.330 --> 15:55.872
But if you say so.

15:57.433 --> 16:07.704
See, back when I became a Christ follower, I was 18 years old and my sexuality was all over the place because I just wasn't following Christ at all.

16:07.744 --> 16:14.130
And then I got saved and I started reading the Bible and Jesus said that I shouldn't even look

16:14.370 --> 16:16.973
at a woman with lust, let alone have sex before marriage.

16:17.814 --> 16:21.218
And I was like, man, that is terrible.

16:21.979 --> 16:23.341
What a terrible rule.

16:23.621 --> 16:24.262
I was at Liberty.

16:24.282 --> 16:26.465
There's all these beautiful single girls everywhere.

16:26.505 --> 16:30.349
And I'm not even allowed to lust after one of them or let alone touch one of them.

16:33.814 --> 16:41.563
And so I went on this two year dating fast because I just needed to learn how to obey Jesus in the area of sexuality.

16:43.065 --> 16:44.146
I started dating Jackie.

16:45.506 --> 16:50.173
We had a conversation and said, we will not have sex until our wedding night if we get married.

16:51.334 --> 16:51.995
It was crazy.

16:52.235 --> 16:52.876
Who does that?

16:54.258 --> 16:59.826
Let alone an 18-year-old, 19-year-old man whose hormones are raging, right?

17:01.208 --> 17:05.654
