19:30.106 --> 19:31.268
God tells Abraham, here's what I'm going to do.

19:31.288 --> 19:31.749
I'm going to bless you.

19:31.769 --> 19:33.452
I'm going to make you the father of many nations.

19:33.733 --> 19:37.841
Your descendants are going to be as numerous as the stars of the sky, as numerous as the sand of the seashore.

19:39.585 --> 19:41.248
Through Isaac, your son, I'm going to give you a son.

19:41.268 --> 19:43.152
Through Isaac, I'm going to bless many nations.

19:44.034 --> 19:45.316
But first, let me test you.

19:45.737 --> 19:48.242
Listen to what God says to Abraham, Genesis chapter 22.

19:48.642 --> 19:50.505
Take your son, your only son.

19:50.585 --> 19:55.031
Yes, Isaac, whom you love so much, and go to the land of Moriah.

19:55.051 --> 19:56.032
And here's what I want you to do.

19:56.533 --> 20:01.439
I want you to offer him as a sacrifice, a burnt offering on one of the mountains I'm gonna show you.

20:01.580 --> 20:01.800
What?

20:03.642 --> 20:15.218
God, you told me that through this boy, Isaac, you're gonna multiply my descendants, and I'm gonna be the father of many, how could you ask me to human sacrifice?

20:15.330 --> 20:18.635
Now, to us, that sounds incredulous, and it is in our culture today.

20:18.995 --> 20:26.405
Back in Abraham's day, all of the pagan religions and pagan people, they would offer their children as sacrifices.

20:26.466 --> 20:29.430
It was very common practice back then to appease the gods.

20:30.571 --> 20:36.359
Now, in this situation, there was no way God was going to fulfill or ask Abraham to go through with it.

20:36.660 --> 20:41.106
He was just testing him to see if he would obey.

20:41.602 --> 20:45.469
So Abraham the next day gets his son, gets some wood, gets his servants together.

20:45.509 --> 20:47.553
They go on a three day hike to Mount Moriah.

20:47.573 --> 20:51.080
They finally get there and they're walking up the mountain and making a long story short here.

20:51.500 --> 20:58.072
Isaac says to his dad, hey dad, we've got the wood, we've got the fire, we've got the knife, like we've got the rope, like we're ready for this burned offering.

20:58.473 --> 20:59.295
Where's the lamb?

21:00.096 --> 21:01.038
Interesting conversation.

21:01.459 --> 21:02.140
You know what Abraham says?

21:02.521 --> 21:03.583
Don't worry, God will provide.

21:04.645 --> 21:05.426
Can you imagine?

21:06.338 --> 21:13.608
Get to the top of the mountain, he grabs his son, puts him on the altar, ties him up, raises the knife, is about ready to take his own son's life.

21:13.688 --> 21:19.275
And all of a sudden the angel of the Lord shows up and says this, don't lay a hand on the boy, the angel said, don't hurt him in any way.

21:19.295 --> 21:27.006
For I know now that you fear God, for you have not withheld your son, your only son from me.

21:28.287 --> 21:29.930
What was God doing in this situation?

21:29.950 --> 21:33.234
Nobody was doing, he was testing Abraham to see if he would obey.

21:34.306 --> 21:39.072
before he gave him even more authority and more influence and more impact.

21:39.092 --> 21:41.456
Can I just say I think the same is true in our lives?

21:43.759 --> 21:51.069
But God wants to upgrade your life, but upgrades require more character, more responsibility, more trust.

21:51.790 --> 21:55.154
Dallas Willard said a few years ago, Jesus is actually looking for people.

21:55.554 --> 21:56.816
that he can trust with his powers.

21:56.916 --> 22:01.162
He wants to give us an upgrade and give us more influence and power.

22:01.583 --> 22:03.085
But can I ask you this question?

22:03.646 --> 22:07.432
Can he trust you with more?

22:08.974 --> 22:14.042
Well, if you're disobedient, if you just skip steps like, ah, I got this.

22:14.583 --> 22:15.584
I know what I'm doing.

22:16.125 --> 22:17.107
I know how to run a business.

22:17.127 --> 22:18.589
I know how to handle finances.

22:18.649 --> 22:19.410
I know how to

22:20.706 --> 22:24.732
Why would he put more in your hands if you're unfaithful with the small things?

22:24.972 --> 22:26.555
He won't do it.

22:27.737 --> 22:28.999
Why does an upgrade lead us?

22:29.419 --> 22:30.941
Why does obedience lead us to an upgrade?

22:30.962 --> 22:36.750
Because God can trust us with more authority and more power and more influence.

22:36.910 --> 22:37.772
That's the second reason.

22:37.792 --> 22:39.014
Let me talk about this third one.

22:40.215 --> 22:47.186
The third reason why obedience leads to an upgrade is because God's way is the best way.

22:47.554 --> 22:48.615
Ways are the best way.

22:48.635 --> 22:49.356
What do I mean by that?

22:49.436 --> 22:50.538
God's ways are the best ways.

22:51.659 --> 22:52.400
Well, he just knows.

22:53.301 --> 22:54.423
He just knows about everything.

22:54.943 --> 22:57.506
Like Jesus created the heavens and the earth.

22:57.927 --> 23:00.911
He knows everything about everything because he made it.

23:01.672 --> 23:04.815
Mathematics, biochemistry, psychology.

23:04.896 --> 23:06.678
You put a topic on the table.

23:07.038 --> 23:10.022
Jesus knows everything about it.

23:10.042 --> 23:13.827
The human brain, the human soul, the whole physical body.

23:13.847 --> 23:14.788
Like he made it.

23:14.968 --> 23:16.530
He's the author, right?

23:16.834 --> 23:23.480
And when you come to a point where it's like, okay, so Jesus, you're not just the dude that died on the cross because you love all people.

23:23.540 --> 23:29.426
You're not just the guy that gets on a knee and the little kids come and sit on your knee and you hug them and you hold a sheep at the same time.

23:29.446 --> 23:30.487
You're not just that guy.

23:30.948 --> 23:35.092
Remember that series that we did?

23:35.112 --> 23:41.778
You are the most brilliant being in the universe.

23:41.818 --> 23:43.259
You know everything about everything.

23:44.441 --> 23:46.002
You are the smartest person.

23:46.882 --> 23:47.343
a life.

23:48.385 --> 23:55.618
You come to that spot in your understanding of Jesus and then you read what he says, you're like, I'll do it.

23:56.640 --> 23:57.041
Yes or no?

23:57.061 --> 23:57.642
Do you agree with that?

23:58.283 --> 23:58.885
Like, I'll do it.

