Why is James saying this?

27:10.309 --> 27:13.832
He's saying this because like, look, my brother knows everything about everything, just do what he says.

27:14.933 --> 27:16.034
That's why James said that.

27:17.836 --> 27:27.946
If you just follow his orders, his instructions, and you don't deviate to the right or to the left, but you continue in them, you will walk in freedom.

27:28.026 --> 27:31.890
One time Jesus put it like this, whoever hears these words, these teachings of mine,

27:32.034 --> 27:35.461
And does them is like a wise person who builds his house on the rock.

27:35.521 --> 27:43.157
And then when the storms of life come in, floods, winds, rains, the house stands firm because it's built on the rock.

27:44.299 --> 27:45.080
How do you build your house?

27:45.121 --> 27:46.263
How do you build your life on the rock?

27:46.283 --> 27:47.325
You do what Jesus says.

27:47.686 --> 27:50.491
On the other hand, whoever hears my words, doesn't do them.

27:50.552 --> 27:53.778
It's like a foolish person who builds his life, his house.

27:53.858 --> 28:02.889
on the beach, on the sand, and all of a sudden the winds and the stresses of life come and money problems and someone dies, and this happens, and that house falls apart.

28:03.129 --> 28:05.912
It collapses why, because it was built on sand.

28:06.493 --> 28:08.015
That's what happens when we say, you know what?

28:08.295 --> 28:09.777
I think I'll skip this step, this step.

28:10.297 --> 28:17.986
We cut parts of the Bible out we don't like, and our house falls, and then we wonder, well, why is my life so messed up?

28:18.927 --> 28:21.330
You've been skipping, skipping, skipping, skipping, skipping.

28:22.946 --> 28:23.708
the instructions.

28:25.492 --> 28:27.618
Jesus knows best.

